===重要事件===
[[File:Brooklynbridge_tablet_200907.jpg|thumb]]
[[File:Aerial_view_looking_down_at_Manhattan_Tower._Jet_Lowe,_photographer,_1982._-_Brooklyn_Bridge,_Spanning_East_River_between_Park_Row,_Manhattan_and_Sands_Street,_Brooklyn,_New_York_HAER_NY,31-NEYO,90-37.tif|thumb]]
[[File:BrooklynBridgeRampsMANH.jpg|thumb]]

* 1915年，纽约市政府正式将大桥命名为布鲁克林大桥<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xdCL5VWmM4MC&pg=PA41&lpg=PA41&dq=Brooklyn+Bridge+naming+1915&source=bl&ots=BQRPSmw1Kl&sig=iJu3mt29V8b7Wgaeoapxj9GSAxY&hl=en&sa=X&ei=ImcdVdvwLdiiyAT-moHQCw&ved=0CGIQ6AEwDQ#v=onepage&q=Brooklyn%20Bridge%20naming%201915&f=false |title=Brooklyn by Name: How the Neighborhoods, Streets, Parks, Bridges, and More ... |accessdate=2015-04-02 |author=Leonard Benardo |author2=Jennifer Weiss |date=2006 |publisher=NYU Press |quote=A Board of Aldermen resolution on January 26, 1915, made it official. |archive-date=2020-04-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200423015331/https://books.google.com/books?id=xdCL5VWmM4MC&pg=PA41&lpg=PA41&dq=Brooklyn+Bridge+naming+1915&source=bl&ots=BQRPSmw1Kl&sig=iJu3mt29V8b7Wgaeoapxj9GSAxY&hl=en&sa=X&ei=ImcdVdvwLdiiyAT-moHQCw&ved=0CGIQ6AEwDQ#v=onepage&q=Brooklyn%20Bridge%20naming%201915&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>，这一名称最早在1867年一月读者致''Brooklyn Daily Eagle''{{NeedZhName}}的信中出现。<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.brooklynpubliclibrary.org/eagle/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071019230402/http://www.brooklynpubliclibrary.org/eagle/ |archivedate=October 19, 2007 |title=Bridging the East River – Another Project |author=E.P.D. |date=1867-01-25 |newspaper=The Brooklyn Daily Eagle |page=2 |accessdate=2007-11-26}}</ref>
* 1919年，Giorgio Pessi{{NeedZhName}}驾驶世界最大飞机之一{{link-en|卡普罗尼Ca.5|Caproni Ca.5}}从桥底飞过。<ref>Franks, Norman et al. (1997) ''Above the War Fronts: The British Two-seater Bomber Pilot and Observer Aces, the British Two-seater Fighter Observer Aces, and the Belgian, Italian, Austro-Hungarian and Russian Fighter Aces, 1914–1918: Volume 4 of Fighting Airmen of WWI Series: Volume 4 of Air Aces of WWI''. Grub Street, 1997. pp. 150-151. ISBN 978-1-898697-56-5, ISBN 978-1-898697-56-5.</ref>
* 1964年，自开通后就成为纽约市标志性建筑物的布鲁克林大桥成为美國[[國家歷史地標|國家歷史地標]]。<ref name="nhlsum"/><ref name="nrhpinv"/><ref name="nrhpphotos"/>
* 1972年，大桥入选[[国际土木工程历史古迹|国际土木工程历史古迹]]。<ref name="Brooklyn Bridge"/>
* 1983年5月24日，大桥建成一百周年，时任美国总统[[罗纳德·里根|罗纳德·里根]]带领着一群游行车队驶过大桥。一群舰队也来到港口检阅，由{{link-en|古奇烟花公司|Grucci Fireworks}}燃放的烟火照亮了大桥上方的夜空。<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nycroads.com/crossings/brooklyn/ | author=NYC Roads | title=The Brooklyn Bridge | accessdate=2010-10-23 | archive-date=2018-12-25 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225040135/http://www.nycroads.com/crossings/brooklyn/%20 | dead-url=yes }}</ref> [[布鲁克林博物馆|布鲁克林博物馆]]展出了一些原先为大桥的建设所作的画作，其中有华盛顿·罗布林的亲手作品。{{link-en|Inc. (杂志)|Inc. (magazine)|Inc.杂志}}將媒体对百年纪念活动的报导称为「1983年的成功公关」。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.inc.com/magazine/19831101/8676.html | work=Inc. | title=Selling the Brooklyn Bridge | first=Curtis | last=Hartman | date=1983-11-01 | accessdate=2012-01-09 | archive-date=2021-03-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210302233413/https://www.inc.com/magazine/19831101/8676.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>
* 1993年6月，{{link-en|蒂埃里·德沃|Thierry Devaux}}在对大桥的金属结构进行了13次勘察后，在一个登山向导的帮助下于东河上方靠近布鲁克林一侧的桥墩的地方（非法）表演了八次[[蹦极|蹦极]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sunnydream.info/index.php?page=brooklyn |title=Brooklyn Bridge |publisher=SunnyDream |accessdate=2010-06-25 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100823234835/http://www.sunnydream.info/index.php?page=brooklyn |archivedate=2010-08-23 }}</ref>
* {{link-en|1994年布鲁克林大桥枪击案|1994 Brooklyn Bridge shooting|1994年3月1日}}，黎巴嫩籍移民拉希德·巴兹（Rashid Baz）在桥上朝载有恰巴德[[犹太教正统派|犹太教正统派]]运动成员的一辆面包车开火，射伤一位16岁学生阿里·哈伯斯塔姆（Ari Halberstam）及三位行人。<ref>{{cite news |title=4 Hasidic Youths Hurt in Brooklyn Bridge Shooting |first=Joe |last=Sexton |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1994/03/02/nyregion/4-hasidic-youths-hurt-in-brooklyn-bridge-shooting.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=1994-03-02 |accessdate=2010-06-30 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308173239/https://www.nytimes.com/1994/03/02/nyregion/4-hasidic-youths-hurt-in-brooklyn-bridge-shooting.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 阿里·哈伯斯塔姆五天后因伤死去。拉希德·巴兹此举显然是在为1994年2月25日发生的[[易卜拉欣大惨案|易卜拉欣大惨案]]中被杀的29位穆斯林复仇。他最终以谋杀罪被判监141年（相当于[[无期徒刑|无期徒刑]]）。此谋杀案原先歸因为[[路怒症|路怒症]]，但[[美国司法部|美国司法部]]于2000年将其重新定性为恐怖袭击。大桥曼哈顿一侧的入口坡道则命名为「阿里·哈伯斯塔姆纪念坡道」以缅怀死者。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arihalberstam.com/in-memoriam/ |title=In Memoriam |publisher=Ari Halberstam Memorial Site |accessdate=2010-06-30 |archive-date=2021-02-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224165445/http://www.arihalberstam.com/in-memoriam/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>
* 2003年，[[美国国家安全局|美国国家安全局]]通过监听[[基地组织|基地组织]]武装分子电话内容及审问，阻止了一场用{{link-en|喷灯|blowtorch}}割断大桥绳索的阴谋。这起事件中，卡车司机{{link-en|法里斯|Iyman Faris}}因向基地组织提供物质援助而被判监20年。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/security/profiles/iyman_faris.htm |title=Iyman Faris |publisher=GlobalSecurity.org |accessdate=2010-06-30 |archive-date=2020-04-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200423015403/https://www.globalsecurity.org/security/profiles/iyman_faris.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>
* 2006年，城市务工人员在曼哈顿一侧的塔楼中发现[[冷战|冷战]]时期留下的地堡。地堡中还存留着为防[[苏联|苏联]]核打击准备的应急救援物资。<ref>{{cite news |title=Cold War "Time Capsule" Found in Brooklyn Bridge |first=Stefan |last=Lovgren |url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2006/03/0324_060324_brooklyn.html |newspaper=National Geographic |date=2006-03-24 |accessdate=2010-02-20 |archive-date=2018-03-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180319131712/https://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2006/03/0324_060324_brooklyn.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>
* 2008年5月24日是布魯克林大橋建成125週年，在22日開始有一連五天的慶祝活動。<ref>[http://news.sina.com.hk/cgi-bin/nw/show.cgi/12/1/1/747629/1.html 新浪網]{{Dead link|date=2019年10月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
* 2011年10月1日，[[占领华尔街|占领华尔街]]行动中，超过700名示威者试图游行穿过大桥，遭到拘捕。<ref>{{cite news |title=Police Arrest More Than 700 Protesters on Brooklyn Bridge |first=Al |last=Baker |first2=Colin |last2=Moynihan |first3=Sarah Maslin |last3=Nir |url=http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/10/01/police-arresting-protesters-on-brooklyn-bridge/ |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2011-10-01 |accessdate=2011-12-11 |archive-date=2011-10-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111021102202/http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/10/01/police-arresting-protesters-on-brooklyn-bridge/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>
* 2014年7月22日早间，有人发现桥上两座塔楼顶端的[[美国国旗|美国国旗]]换成漂白过的美国国旗。据信，作案的几个人当时遮住照亮旗帜的灯光，然后沿着悬索爬上了塔楼。此事件的动机尚未得到确认，但有迹象表明白旗是为了象征投降。<ref>[http://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/White-Flags-Brooklyn-Bridge-American-268110482.html American Flags Bleached White Appear Atop Brooklyn Bridge] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/White-Flags-Brooklyn-Bridge-American-268110482.html |date=20190825062028 }} | NBC New York | Retrieved July 23, 2014</ref><ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-28427078 White flags stump New York police] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-28427078 |date=20210308060231 }} | BBC News | Retrieved July 23, 2014</ref><ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2014/07/23/nyregion/white-flags-mysteriously-appear-atop-the-brooklyn-bridge.html A Brooklyn Bridge Mystery: Who Raised the White Flags?] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/07/23/nyregion/white-flags-mysteriously-appear-atop-the-brooklyn-bridge.html |date=20201112020032 }} | The New York Times | Retrieved July 23, 2014</ref>  警方查看了监控录像并比对DNA，截至2014年8月1日，共确认了9名「嫌疑人」，而可能的动机则是[[大麻|大麻]]激进主义。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nypost.com/2014/08/01/cops-closing-in-on-brooklyn-bridge-white-flag-suspects/|title=Cops closing in on Brooklyn Bridge white flag suspects|work=New York Post|date=August 1, 2014|accessdate=August 2, 2014|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308175940/https://nypost.com/2014/08/01/cops-closing-in-on-brooklyn-bridge-white-flag-suspects/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2014年8月12日，两名柏林艺术家米沙·莱因考夫（Mischa Leinkauf）和马蒂亚斯·韦姆克（Matthias Wermke）声称为此事及其引起的恐慌负责。两人称旗帜是为了庆祝「公共空间之美」以及纪念大桥的设计者{{link-en|約翰·奧古斯塔斯·羅布林|John Augustus Roebling|约翰·罗布林}}。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/cheats/2014/08/12/germans-put-flags-on-brooklyn-bridge.html|title=Germans Put Flags on Brooklyn Bridge|work=Daily Beast|date=August 12, 2014|accessdate=August 12, 2014|archive-date=2016-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221185652/http://www.thedailybeast.com/cheats/2014/08/12/germans-put-flags-on-brooklyn-bridge.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-28770540 | title = Artists Claim Brooklyn Bridge Stunt | work = BBC News | accessdate = August 13, 2014 | archive-date = 2021-03-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210307221658/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-28770540 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/German-Artists-Claim-White-Flags-Brooklyn-Bridge-270977621.html | title = Artists Claim White Flags on Bridge | work = NBC New York | accessdate = August 13, 2014 | archive-date = 2019-06-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190609034218/https://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/German-Artists-Claim-White-Flags-Brooklyn-Bridge-270977621.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>

历史上也有过几位著名的跳桥者。第一个从大桥上跳下的人是{{link-en|罗伯特·埃米特·奥德隆|Robert Emmet Odlum}}，他于1885年5月19日跳桥，是女权积极分子{{link-en|夏洛特·奥德隆·史密斯|Charlotte Odlum Smith}}的兄弟。<ref name="Odlum">{{cite book |url= http://books.google.com/books?id=FP4NAQAAIAAJ |title= The Life and Adventures of Prof. Robert Emmet Odlum, Containing an Account of his Splendid Natatorium at the National Capital |year= 1885 |author= Catherine Odlum |publisher= Gray and Clarkson |access-date= 2015-02-11 |archive-date= 2014-07-10 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140710193256/http://books.google.com/books?id=FP4NAQAAIAAJ |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref name="Stanley">{{cite book | author = Stanley, Autumn | authorlink =  | year = 2009 | title = Raising More Hell and Fewer Dahlias: The Public Life of Charlotte Smith, 1840–1917 | location = Bethlehem, Pennsylvania|Bethlehem | publisher = Lehigh University Press | isbn = 978-0-934223-99-7}}</ref> 他撞向水面后不久便因内伤而死。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=990DE4D91739E533A25753C2A9639C94649FD7CF|newspaper=The New York Times|title=Odlum's Leap to Death|date=May 20, 1885|page=1|accessdate=April 15, 2008|archive-date=2016-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305081421/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=990DE4D91739E533A25753C2A9639C94649FD7CF|dead-url=no}}</ref> {{link-en|史蒂夫·布罗迪|Steve Brodie (bridge jumper)}}则是最有名的跳桥者，或说是自称的跳桥者（1886年）。漫画家Otto Eppers{{NeedZhName}}1910年跳桥但得以生还，后因自杀未遂受审并无罪释放。<ref>Abstract of [http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F40A10FC395417738DDDA90B94DE405B808DF1D3 "Youth Dives Off Brooklyn Bridge; Youngster Eludes the Police and Plunges Into the East River, Escaping Unhurt"] {{Wayback|url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F40A10FC395417738DDDA90B94DE405B808DF1D3 |date=20131203114227 }}, ''[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]', n.d.</ref>

